<HEADLINE> Green Returns to Blue Jays Lineup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Shawn Green, who returned to the Blue Jays'  
lineup after missing a week because of a small fracture in his left 
wrist, left Friday's game against Montreal in the fifth inning. 
</P>
<P>
	Green sustained the injury after being hit by a pitch in the  
fourth inning May 28 against the New York Yankees. He went 0-for-2 
with a strikeout and a flyout and seemed to be clenching the hand 
during the game, which Toronto won 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't want to a wait a couple of weeks until it's complete  
healed,'' Green said before the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Toronto lost five of six while he was out.  
</P>
<P>
	``It's going to be sore, and if it gets too bad I'm not going to  
play,'' said Green, who only took a few swings in batting practice 
so as not to aggravate it. ``Right now I feel I can do it. It's 
better to get out there and play than to sit and watch.'' 
  	   	
</P>
