<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange, American Stock 
Exchange and Nasdaq Stock Market. 

</P>
<P>
 *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
	Procter &AMP; Gamble, up 3 1/8 at 96 5/8  
</P>
<P>
	The Cincinnati-based consumer products company plans to cut  
thousands of jobs, close plants and take a charge of up to $3 
billion to become more competitive in its second major 
reorganization in six years, according to published reports. 

</P>
<P>
	Nu Skin Enterprises, down 1/16 at 17 13/16  
</P>
<P>
	The Provo, Utah-based direct seller expects its second-quarter  
earnings to be 10 percent below Wall Street analysts' predictions. 

</P>
<P>
	Circuit City Stores, up 6 3/4 at 81 7/8  
</P>
<P>
	The Richmond, Va.-based company expects earnings will be  
substantially above analysts' expectations for its core Circuit 
City consumer electronics business because of strong first-quarter 
sales. 

</P>
<P>
	Sports Authority, down 7/16 at 4 13/16  
</P>
<P>
	The Fort Lauderdale, Fla.-based sporting goods retailer reported  
late Thursday that its same-store sales in May fell 6.4 percent. 
Same-store sales include stores open at least a year and are 
considered an industry gauge of performance. 

</P>
<P>
	Smedvig, down 1 1/4 at 8 3/4  
</P>
<P>
	Norwegian energy concern Statoil AS has canceled a contract with  
shipping company Smedvig for the deep water drilling ship West 
Navion. Smedvig said Statoil canceled the contract due to delays in 
getting the ship ready for drilling. 

</P>
<P>
 *NASDAQ   	
</P>
<P>
	Guitar Center, down 4 1/8 at 10 15/16  
</P>
<P>
	The retailer said its merger with Musician's Friend Inc. will  
dilute earnings for the final three quarters of 1999 by 8 cents a 
share and current business trends will lower earnings by another 2 
cents a share. 

</P>
<P>
	Avery Dennison, up 7/8 at 62 7/8 on the NYSE  
</P>
<P>
	Stimsonite, up 4 at 14 1/2  
</P>
<P>
	Avery, a maker of self-adhesive labels and stamps, will acquire  
Stimsonite for $137 million, or $14.75 a share. Stimsonite makes 
highway safety products to improve drivers' visual guidance. 

</P>
<P>
	Visx, up 17 1/8 at 71 7/8  
</P>
<P>
	The company, which specializes in refractive laser technology,  
said that a Federal Trade Commission administrative law judge has 
dismissed an FTC complaint related to a patent of Visx's laser 
vision correction. 

</P>
<P>
	Quantum, down 9/16 at 19  
</P>
<P>
	The computer disk-drive maker expects its first-quarter earnings  
to fall below Wall Street analysts' estimates. 

</P>
<P>
	Beyond.com, up 4 13/16 at 22 1/4  
</P>
<P>
	The Internet software retailer along with ITC of Fairfax, Va.,  
received a 65-month, $120 million contract by the Internal Revenue 
Service for the electronic delivery and maintenance of Microsoft 
software to 130,000 computers within the agency. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
