<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Police Find Slain Ohio Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BAVINGTON, Pa. (AP) -- The bodies of two missing college students  
were found in a wooded area Friday, and police believe they were 
kidnapped during a burglary, robbed and shot to death. 
</P>
<P>
	Before the bodies were found, three people were charged with the  
robbery-related crimes. Police said two were suspected in the 
students' deaths. No charges were filed because police were holding 
out hope the victims were still alive. 
</P>
<P>
	Police and 100 volunteers including troopers on horseback picked  
through briar patches, waist-high grass and swamps along 11 miles 
of highway here for three days before finding the bodies of Aaron 
Land, 20, and Brian Muha, 18. 
</P>
<P>
	Both were students at Franciscan University in Steubenville,  
Ohio, 15 miles west of here and a short distance from the 
Pennsylvania-West Virginia line. 
</P>
<P>
	On Friday morning, Ohio authorities charged Terrell Rhaim  
Yarbrough, 18, of Pittsburgh and Nathan D. Herring, 18, of 
Steubenville, Ohio, with kidnapping, burglary and robbery. Both 
were being held on more than $2 million bond. 
</P>
<P>
	A third suspect, 16-year-old Brandon Young of Steubenville,  
Ohio, was charged in juvenile court with receiving stolen property. 
He was held without bond. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials will seek capital murder charges from a grand jury,  
mostly likely in Ohio, even though the victims were shot in 
southwestern Pennsylvania, said Stephen Stern, a prosecutor in 
Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
	Police believe Land and Muha were kidnapped Monday from their  
apartment during a burglary, robbed and shot to death. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
