<HEADLINE> Dollar Up, Japanese Stocks Mixed / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar edged up against the yen today and the  
euro continued to draw investors's attention in Asian trading. 
Tokyo share prices were mixed in light trading. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 121.62 yen in late afternoon trading, up 0.08  
yen from late Thursday in Tokyo but lower than its late New York 
level of 121.66 yen overnight. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 73.25  
points, or 0.45 percent, closing at 16,300.75 points. On Thursday, 
the index shed 190.49 points, or 1.16 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency dealings, the dollar moved narrowly against the yen  
and the euro continued its slide on pessimism on Europe's economy 
and the possibility of peace in Kosovo. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro hit a record low against the dollar early in the Asian  
session today on aggressive selling by overseas funds, falling to 
$1.0270. It later settled into a range around $1.0300. In Tokyo 
trading, the euro was quoted at 125.29 yen, down from 125.95 yen 
late Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Overseas funds heavily sold the euro on the view that European  
economic fundamentals will remain poor,'' said a dealer at a 
European bank who spoke on condition of anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar ranged between 121.44 yen and 121.75 yen in today's  
trading. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, the Nikkei average gained some ground on selective  
buying, but the market as a whole was mixed at the end of the day's 
trading. The market lacked fresh market-moving news, traders said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Players are waiting for incentives to trade shares,'' said  
Sachio Ishikawa, general manager of the stock division at Chuo 
Securities. 
</P>
<P>
	Traders still hope that the government will map out additional  
steps to buoy Japan's economy, in its worst recession since World 
War II. 
</P>
<P>
	Volume on the exchange's first section was estimated at 369  
million shares, compared with Thursday's turnover of 359 million. 
Advancers outnumbered decliners 636 to 528, with 124 issues 
unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section edged down 1.16 points, or 0.09 percent, to 1,316.53. 
The TOPIX finished down 9.08 points, or 0.68 percent, the day 
before. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark No. 213 10-year Japanese government  
bond rose to 1.6400 percent from Thursday's finish of 1.6050 
percent, driving its price down to 97.93 yen from 98.23 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
