<HEADLINE> Report: Rivers To Get $8M, 4 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Doc Rivers has reached agreement on a  
four-year, $8 million deal to become coach of the Orlando Magic, 
according to ESPN and the Orlando Sentinel. 
</P>
<P>
	A team spokesman, however, said the club had not finalized  
anything with the former guard who played 13 NBA seasons and is now 
a television analyst. The Sentinel reported Rivers, 37, will sign 
Monday. 
</P>
