<HEADLINE> Boy Kills Brother Over Video Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANCHORAGE, Alaska (AP) -- A 5-year-old boy shot his brother to  
death following an argument over a video game, police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Joseph Pitka, 7, died Thursday after his brother shot him once  
in the head with a .22-caliber rifle that had been left loaded in 
the house. 
</P>
<P>
	Trooper spokesman Greg Wilkinson said one adult, a friend of the  
family, was in the house at the time of the shooting but was 
sleeping. The brothers' 3-year-old sister was home. 
</P>
<P>
	The boys had been fighting over who got to play with a video  
game, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Wilkinson said the younger boy, whose name was not released,  
will not be charged. But charges may be brought against adults in 
the case, he said. 
  	   	
</P>
