<HEADLINE> Three Ring Captures Acorn Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Three Ring, who finished last in the Kentucky  
Derby, withstood a foul claim on Friday to capture the $200,000 
Acorn Stakes by a head at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Jerry Bailey, Three Ring won for the third time in  
five starts this year. She was the odds-on favorite in the Grade I 
race for 3-year-old fillies. 
</P>
<P>
	Better Than Honour was tough in the stretch but settled for  
second in the eight-horse field. Madison's Charm was another 
half-length back in third. 
</P>
<P>
	After the horses crossed the finish line, Better Than Honour  
jockey Richard Migliore said Three Ring interfered in the final 
furlong. 
</P>
<P>
	A review showed Three Ring drifting out under Bailey's  
left-handed whip. The filly apparently bumped Better Than Honor and 
forced her wide, but the stewards deemed the jostling insufficient. 
</P>
<P>
	The Florida-bred filly previously scored decisive victories  
against her own sex in Gulfstream Park's Grade II Bonnie Miss and 
Davona Dale stakes. She finished 19th in the Kentucky Derby. 
</P>
<P>
	Three Ring carried 121 pounds, as did all the starters. She  
covered the mile in 1:36 on a fast track to earn $120,000 for owner 
Barry Schwartz. 
</P>
<P>
	The Acorn is the first leg of the New York Racing Association's  
Triple Tiara series for 3-year-old fillies. The other legs are the 
Mother Goose Stakes on June 26 and the Coaching Club American Oaks 
on July 24. 
</P>
<P>
	Three Ring returned $3.80, $2.90 and $2.60. Better Than Honour  
paid $5.10 and $4.20 and Madison's Charm showed at $4.20. 
</P>
<P>
	In the co-feature, the $82,075 Fashion Stakes for 2-year-olds,  
More Than Ready won by a head and is unbeaten in three career 
starts. The odds-on choice carried 119 pounds and was ridden by 
John Velazquez. 
</P>
<P>
	Diablo's Addition was second in the field of six, finishing 5 3/4  
lengths ahead of Bevo. 
</P>
<P>
	More Than Ready went five furlongs in :57 to earn $49,245 for  
owner James Scatuorchio. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $3.30, $2.50 and $2.10. Diablo's Addition  
paid $6.40 and $2.10 and Bevo showed at $2.10. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
