<DOCNO> APW19990604.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-04 13:40:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Welcomes Mexico Court Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The State Department welcomed a ruling by  
Mexico's supreme court that a man suspected of being a top drug 
trafficker can be extradited to the United States to face charges 
if he is arrested by Mexican police. 
</P>
<P>
	The ruling involves Miguel Caro Quintero, said to control a  
large portion of drug trafficking along Mexico's northwestern 
border with the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	``The ability to hit the leadership of these drug-trafficking  
organizations is critical to the success of our joint strategy,'' 
State Department spokesman James P. Rubin said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Bringing such criminals to justice in Mexico and in the U.S.  
is of paramount importance,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Thursday's Mexican court ruling upheld a lower court decision in  
the case. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
