<HEADLINE> Soccer: Germany 6, Moldova 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEVERKUSEN, Germany (AP) -- Oliver Bierhoff snapped his  
384-minute scoreless streak with three goals Friday in Germany's 
6-1 rout of Moldova in a qualifier for next year's European 
Championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Germany, started four forwards, attacked from the opening  
seconds as Bierhoff's shot ricocheted off the crossbar just 48 
seconds into the match. He scored in the second, 56th and 81st 
minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Ulf Kirsten, Marco Bode and Mehmet Scholl also scored for  
Germany (4-1), which leads Group Three. Gheorghe Stratulat scored 
in the 76th minute for Moldova (0-4-2), which is last in the 
five-team group. 
</P>
<P>
	In Friday's only other game, Poland beat Bulgaria 2-0 at Warsaw  
on goals by Tomasz Hajto in the 16th minute and Tomasz Iwan in the 
62nd. Poland (3-2) is second in Group Five, three points behind 
Sweden (4-0). Bulgaria (1-3-1) is fourth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
